      "id": "8d6c7f2a-2d6a-4d2f-9d5f-4b5b8d3b9d21",
      "title": "OSPF Area Types & LSA Flooding",
      "category": "routing",
      "body_markdown": "Area 0 — backbone area.\n\nStub areas suppress external LSAs. NSSA allows limited external redistribution via Type-7 LSAs.\n\nKey idea: understanding how LSAs are flooded helps you predict convergence behavior.",
      "code_blocks": [
        {
          "lang": "bash",
          "content": "router ospf 1\n area 1 stub no-summary"
        }
      ],
      "images": [
